1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:04,530
A responsive website, changes based
on the characteristics of the device.

2
00:00:04,530 --> 00:00:06,600
This means, that your responsive site,

3
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:09,920
needs to apply different styles,
for different devices.

4
00:00:10,930 --> 00:00:14,150
There are few ways to
selectively apply CSS.

5
00:00:14,150 --> 00:00:17,010
The easiest, is with media queries.

6
00:00:17,010 --> 00:00:19,470
Media queries, provide easy logic for

7
00:00:19,470 --> 00:00:23,100
applying different styles depending
on device characteristics.

8
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:28,170
Like its width, height,
or device pixel ratio.

9
00:00:28,170 --> 00:00:29,510
You can change everything,

10
00:00:29,510 --> 00:00:33,830
from background images to restructuring
the site's layout and even more.

11
00:00:33,830 --> 00:00:36,070
Adding responsive styles is easy.

12
00:00:36,070 --> 00:00:40,540
Simply include an additional style
sheet in your page, with a media query.

13
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:41,460
Let me show you how to write one.
